spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of the week, I click my “board cleanup” link, and it returns each card to its\noriginal project board.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"YwzluNh9Mp"}],"key":"aJtIDw5DbJ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next week, I repeat this cycle.","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"uzdY339dIf"}],"key":"UNoaA9wKBf"}],"key":"XyCZlUr2LZ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And that’s about it - I’ve found that this process is a nice way to keep both a high-level\nview of what needs to be done for my various projects (on each project board). It also allows\nmy to dig into specific to-do items throughout the week (on my weekly board).","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"b5PHQNo8As"}],"key":"Y3mJXE8z1B"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":126,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’d love to hear feedback and thoughts about how other people manage their time throughout\nthe week! Hopefully some of you all find this useful.","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"GOTWM9FVNg"}],"key":"KvGSze1fxB"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Extras","position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"key":"Hmc70wVuUl"}],"identifier":"extras","label":"Extras","html_id":"extras","implicit":true,"key":"TyoEOmBA2G"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":131,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Butler for Trello commands can be a little bit difficult to compose. Below I’ll post the\ntwo main commands that I use to handle all the card-moving described above.","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"key":"UFtVY6tKxr"}],"key":"X6yxuZBTCP"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board","position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"key":"TCSELVRuVt"}],"identifier":"the-weekly-board","label":"The weekly board","html_id":"the-weekly-board","implicit":true,"key":"vP4Syv7BcR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":136,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board has a “butler” list where the command is defined in a card (that’s how\nyou define board-specific BFT commands). Here’s the command:","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"key":"iEGt45JnzO"}],"key":"D9AahhSZoy"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":138,"column":1},"end":{"line":138,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{% raw %}","position":{"start":{"line":138,"column":1},"end":{"line":138,"column":1}},"key":"cyE7L5ECry"}],"key":"ovxyMWz5Cr"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"script: for each card in list \"Return\", remove all labels and move the card to list \"Returned | Week {weeknumber}\" on board \"{{%homeboard}}\" and move list \"Returned | Week {weeknumber}\" on board \"{{%homeboard}}\" to position 1 and clear custom field \"homeboard\"","position":{"start":{"line":139,"column":1},"end":{"line":141,"column":1}},"key":"QDn2l9GaZ3"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{% endraw %}","position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"key":"KyEhZh4Ljs"}],"key":"bCLuOqU79a"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A global command for project boards","position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"key":"zgUpYBZDe0"}],"identifier":"a-global-command-for-project-boards","label":"A global command for project boards","html_id":"a-global-command-for-project-boards","implicit":true,"key":"MTpHxqbRjx"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I also use a global BFT command that moves the cards from each project board to the weekly\nboard when the card is moved to the “Doing” category.","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"key":"RW3LarhteY"}],"key":"lzryH74EAA"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"when a card is added to list \"Doing\" by me, set custom field \"homeboard\" to \"{boardlink}\" and move the card to the top of list \"{boardname}\" on board \"Active\" and move list \"{boardname}\" on board \"Active\" to position 2","position":{"start":{"line":149,"column":1},"end":{"line":151,"column":1}},"key":"mHpzeZ6JTE"}],"key":"ZxTXSteg78"}],"key":"nMaANDlt0S"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Introducing makeitpop, a tool to perceptually warp your data!\"","url":"/blog/2018/makeitpop","group":"2018"},"next":{"title":"I like Rust’s governance structure","url":"/blog/2018/rust-governance","group":"2018"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}